## OWASP Top 10 baseline (already on)

- **A01** — backend authoritative; client guards UX only
- **A02** — session cookies (HttpOnly) — never JWT in localStorage
- **A03** — React auto-escape; `react/no-danger` ESLint banned
- **A05** — same-origin rewrites in `next.config.ts`; strict response headers (`X-Frame-Options=DENY`, `Permissions-Policy` denies camera/mic/geolocation/payment)
- **A06** — `pnpm audit --prod` in CI; pinned majors
- **A08** — lockfile committed
- **A09** — `productionBrowserSourceMaps: false`

## Adding what you need

```bash
pnpm add @radix-ui/themes @radix-ui/react-icons  # Radix Themes UI
pnpm add zustand                                  # state mgmt
pnpm add @tanstack/react-query                    # server state
pnpm add zod                                      # validation
pnpm add -D vitest @testing-library/react jsdom   # tests
pnpm add -D @playwright/test                      # E2E
```

For Next.js App Router + Server Components, you can:
- Keep the existing **session-cookie / allauth-headless** pattern from the [React Full template](https://github.com/Axionore/Django-Barkery) (Client Components only — fetches go through Next's rewrites).
- Or use Server Actions to call the Django backend server-side, forwarding the session cookie.

Either way: **never store a token in `localStorage`** — that's an OWASP A02 anti-pattern.

## Calling the backend

```tsx
// Client Component
"use client";
async function fetchMe() {
  const res = await fetch("/api/me", { credentials: "include" });
  if (!res.ok) throw new Error(res.statusText);
  return res.json();
}
```

```ts
// Server Component / Server Action — forward the cookie from the incoming request
import { cookies } from "next/headers";

export async function GET() {
  const cookieStore = await cookies();
  const sessionId = cookieStore.get("sessionid")?.value;
  const csrf = cookieStore.get("csrftoken")?.value;
  const res = await fetch(`${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL}/api/me`, {
    headers: {
      Cookie: `sessionid=${sessionId}; csrftoken=${csrf}`,
    },
  });
  return Response.json(await res.json());
}
```

Backend auth model: **session cookies**. For Ninja: [`django_auth`](https://django-ninja.dev/guides/authentication/). For DRF: [`SessionAuthentication`](https://www.django-rest-framework.org/api-guide/authentication/).
